pdc_describe.title: Error uploading README

comments.body:
For some reason the column `url` in the `upload_snapshots` in Staging is marked as NOT NULLABLE but our definition in the code and in our local environments allow for NULLs.

Looking at the history of this table we have upgraded this table and field in the past (https://github.com/pulibrary/pdc_describe/blob/main/db/migrate/20230503142628_snapshot_uri.rb) and I am wondering if something did not get applied in staging in one of those upgrades.

I fixed the table directly in staging via the following commands in `psql`

Connect to Postgres (get the connection values from `env | grep APP_DB`)

```
$ psql -h hhh -U uuu -d ddd
```

Check the `upload_snapshots` table, notice that field `url` is NOT nullable:

```
pdc_describe_staging=> \d upload_snapshots
                                          Table "public.upload_snapshots"
   Column   |              Type              | Collation | Nullable |                   Default
------------+--------------------------------+-----------+----------+----------------------------------------------
 id         | bigint                         |           | not null | nextval('upload_snapshots_id_seq'::regclass)
 url        | character varying              |           | not null |
 work_id    | bigint                         |           | not null |
 created_at | timestamp(6) without time zone |           | not null |
 updated_at | timestamp(6) without time zone |           | not null |
 version    | bigint                         |           |          |
 files      | jsonb                          |           |          |
 type       | character varying              |           |          |
```

Update the table to make the field nullable:

```
pdc_describe_staging=> ALTER TABLE upload_snapshots ALTER COLUMN url DROP NOT NULL;
ALTER TABLE

pdc_describe_staging=> \d upload_snapshots
                                          Table "public.upload_snapshots"
   Column   |              Type              | Collation | Nullable |                   Default
------------+--------------------------------+-----------+----------+----------------------------------------------
 id         | bigint                         |           | not null | nextval('upload_snapshots_id_seq'::regclass)
 url        | character varying              |           |          |
 work_id    | bigint                         |           | not null |
 created_at | timestamp(6) without time zone |           | not null |
 updated_at | timestamp(6) without time zone |           | not null |
 version    | bigint                         |           |          |
 files      | jsonb                          |           |          |
 type       | character varying              |           |          |
 ```
Applied the same fix in the production database as well.
